Mario Balotelli has joined his hometown club, Brescia, on a free transfer, the Serie A side confirmed on Sunday. Balotelli, who was released by Marseille at the end of last season, returns to Italy for his third stint. The controversial striker has previously played for Inter Milan, where he won three league titles and AC Milan. The 29-year-old Italian will be presented at the Stadio Mario Rigamonti later on Monday. Balotelli has signed a three-year deal with Brescia, who are back in the top flight for the first time since 2011. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.